        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/b77776/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-01T11:47:25.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The impressive part is how well they do in this vintage. The 11 Chev was my number 1 wine at the tasting but the 13 Chassagne-Montrachet is what made me a believer.  Good from the bottom up and in tough vintages. Almost like a cross between Ramonet and PYCM. Fine balance but plenty of power and length.</p>",
